Introduces the technique of setting the value of a
boolean variable to a boolean expression, thereby
potentially negating the need for unnecessary code.


Went from

    int income = 120_000;
    boolean hasHighIncome;

    if (income > 100_000)
        hasHighIncome = true;
    else
        hasHighIncome = false;


to


    int income = 120_000;
    boolean hasHighIncome = false;

    if (income > 100_000)
            hasHighIncome = true;



to


    int income = 120_000;
    boolean hasHighIncome = (income > 100_000);




